                            <comment id="13826138" author="jdere" created="Tue, 19 Nov 2013 03:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch v1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getColumns(): column_size, decimal_digits, num_prec_radix should use the proper type info for char/varchar/decimal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getColumns(): column_size set to 29 for timestamp, to match JDBC ResultSetMetadata&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getColumns() and ResultSetMetadata should return same scale for timestamp (9).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changed radix to 10 for all numeric types; was previously set to 2 for float/double&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
